   <head>RHYMES.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">work brings after ease;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ease brings sport and sport brings rest;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For young and old of all degrees,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The mingled lot is best.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And pain brings pity; then I hear</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My mother's sweet and gentle voice,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">She strokes my cheek, the touch is dear,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And makes my heart rejoice.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then welcome work and pain and play</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When all is o'er, like bird in nest</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">We soundly sleep; â€” well says our lay,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The mingled lot is best.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
